Heat large skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground beef, onion and bell pepper; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until beef is no longer pink and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and salt Add remaining ingredients except shredded cheese to skillet, stir well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is fully cooked and liquid has absorbed, about 20 minutes. Once rice is cooked, stir in cheese Remove from heat and spoon into bowls. Top with a dollop of sour cream and chopped green onion if desired; serve.